---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="What this blog is and how it's made"
	pubDate={new Date('March 01 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		This blog is a record of things I'm building, breaking, and figuring out — mostly in my home lab
		and with software. The ideas, projects, and experiences here are my own.
	</p>

	<p>
		What's different about this blog is that I'm building it openly with AI. I use AI tools —
		primarily Claude — to help with development, writing, and editing. That includes the code
		powering this site and the prose in these posts. I'm not hiding that; it's actually part of what
		I want to explore and document.
	</p>

	<p>
		The way I think about it: I bring the curiosity, the problems, and the real-world context. AI
		helps me move faster, get unstuck, and write more clearly than I would on my own. The
		combination is more interesting to me than either alone.
	</p>

	<p>
		If you're reading a post here, you're seeing what that collaboration looks like in practice.
	</p>
</Layout>
